            "type": "text",
            "text": "{¥"success¥":true,¥"process_rule_id¥":¥"J09C¥",¥"process_rule¥":¥"1. Copy the decision table into table `J09C_temp` for all records where the tour starts with `J09C`.¥¥n¥¥n2. Add column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to table `J09C_temp`.¥¥n¥¥n3. Classify the meter reading type in `ENTSCHEIDUNG` using these rules:¥¥n   - If a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = ¥¥¥"KSA¥¥¥"`.¥¥n   - Else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = ¥¥¥"EVU¥¥¥"`.¥¥n   - Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` to `ENTSCHEIDUNG = ¥¥¥"EVU¥¥¥"`.¥¥n   - Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` from `500` to `599` to `ENTSCHEIDUNG = ¥¥¥"EVU¥¥¥"`.¥¥n   - Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` from `900` to `999` to `ENTSCHEIDUNG = ¥¥¥"EVU¥¥¥"`.¥¥n¥¥n4. Join the table with `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.¥¥n¥¥n5. Join the table with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.¥¥n¥¥n6. Compare customer sales master data and net master data.¥¥n¥¥n7. If sales customer data is not empty:¥¥n   1. Use sales customer data table entries.¥¥n   Else:¥¥n   1. Use net data customer table entries.¥¥n¥¥n8. Export the final data as CSV file named `J09C`. Use exactly these column names:¥¥n   - `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`¥¥n   - `HAUS`¥¥n   - `ANLAGE`¥¥n   - `ME_MA_ID`¥¥n   - `EQUNR`¥¥n   - `HOUSE_NUM1`¥¥n   - `ENTSCHEIDUNG`¥¥n   - `TITLE`¥¥n   - `FORENAME`¥¥n   - `SURNAME`¥¥n   - `STREET`¥¥n   - `STREETNO`¥¥n   - `POST_CODE1`¥¥n   - `CITY1`¥¥n   - `CITY2`¥¥n   - `EMAIL`¥¥n¥¥n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the exported CSV file attached. Use file path: `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`.¥¥n¥¥n10. Delete the temporary table.¥"}",
            "id": "lc_e6c00183-982f-4059-a0b9-bf8127bbaca5"
          }
